description: Dr. Doom embarks with Wire to a safeguard island consisted of some of his machinery and personal armory with a vengeful Tyger Wylde in pursuit to killing them both. Poet and Fortune mettle with a digitized angel and a rival of Dr. Doom's past entraps him in his own time portal.
name: Island of Lost Souls

description: Scooby and the gang take a trip to New York City to investigate all of the strange and mysterious things that are happening in the big city’s subway system in “I’ll Take Manhattan.”

When the Mystery, Inc. gang visits the rodeo, they can't decide which is scarier--the shadowy ghost, or the rootin'-tootin' rodeo clowns. The back-up story is scary in a different way, as Scooby lands alone on a South Pacific island and is mistaken for the legendary enemy of...the Volcano Demon!

The ghost of a '60s rock star is groovin' to go a-ghostin' in this month's issue! Join Fred, Velma, Daphne, Shaggy and Scoob for another haunting--and many Scooby Snacks--in "Big Puce!" Written by Joe Staton and Chris Duffy. Art by Manny Galan and Tim Harkins.

Shaggy's gotta have it! No, not Scooby snacks--the latest video game! But can the gang brave the (gulp) ghost to get Shag and Scoob the Christmas present of their dreams? Plus monster museum mayhem and more!

When Shaggy’s uncle Henry Rogers, a famous archaeologist, vanishes while investigating an Egyptian pyramid, Scooby and the gang travel to Cairo to find out what happened in “The Curse of the Scary Scarab.” Issue also has “Psychic Psyche-Out” in which Scooby and the gang investigate a psychic fair.
name: The Curse of the Scary Scarab

description: Get down and get funky with the Phantom of the Mosh Pit! Can Mystery Inc. resolve the riddle of a boogying bogie before he discoes Daphne's pal's dance club to its doom? Plus, an ancient Irish feud leads to ghosts, ghosts and more ghosts in a creepy underground cavern in "The Caves of Castle Finn!"
Concluding the 2-part "One Night in Roswell!" Has the Mystery Inc. gang been sucked into an intergalactic war? Do they even have Scooby snacks in outer space?
name: One Night In Roswell, Part 3: Flying Saucer Face-Off!

description: It's environmentalists versus developers in the Florida Everglades, and Mystery Inc. is in the middle! Plus: Scooby goes undercover in the most unlikely setting of all: high school!

In a tale from the wild, wild west, maverick government agent Bart Simpson, along with master of disguise Martimus Prince, must put a stop to the world?threatening and earth- shattering schemes of Dr. Ralph Braneless. In other stories, Lisa matches wits with Principal Skinner in a Springfield Elementary whodunit, and Bart and Milhouse take the school day off.

  1. Wild, Wild Bart (Bart in the Wild West)
  2. The Case Of The Hanging Shoes (The Secret Files Of Lisa Simpson : who put Martin's shoes over the power lines?)
  3. Bart Simpson's Day Off (will Bart and Milhouse get caught playing hooky?)
  4. Bart's Puzzle Page
  5. Bart's People (letters and fan art)
name: Menace to Society

description: Also includes Welcome to Heaven, Dr. Franklin pt. 6 By William Messner-Loebs

Astrid faces the toughest decision of her life, and she does it alone, estranged from both friends and family. But sheís not aware that Morgana is planning to make that decision much, much easier... by killing her.

Overview

Proof arrives just in time to prevent another murder, but El Chupacabra’s been waiting for him and she has a few surprises under her skin.

As Batman brings Black Mask and The Joker to justice, we all wonder did Stephanie Brown have to die? and if so, was there no way to save her?

description:
Overview

Written and illustrated by Tony Millionaire, Danny Hellman, Roger Langridge, Kyle Baker, Evan Dorkin, Hunt Emerson, Farel Dalrymple, Dylan Horrocks, Eddie Campbell, Dave Cooper, Harvey Pekar, Dean Haspiel, James Kochalka, Tom Hart, Leela Corman, Gilbert Hernandez, Peter Bagge, Derek Kirk Kim, Dave Roman, Raina Telgemeier, Kurt Wolfgang, Brian Ralph, Scott Morse, Ben Dunn, Andi Watson, Bob Fingerman, Paul Grist, Carol Lay, Craig Thompson, Ivan Brunetti, cover by Jaime Hernandez.

Where else could the world;s greatest alternative cartoonists run rampant through the DC Universe in an all-new anthology of utterly unhinged stories and art? It could only happen in the Bizarro World. This big slab o' comics features work by many of the fantastic creators who worked on the Bizarro Comics book (and made it an award-winner). This time the contibutors weaving strange and wonderful tales about the quirky Bizarro include Tony Millionaire, Kyle Baker, Evan Dorkin, Dylan Horrocks, Harvey Pekar, James Kochalka, Peter Bagge, Scott Morse, Ben Dunn and a host of others, along with some double-secret surprise guests.
name: Bizarro World

description:
Overview

Lionel Zerb continues to hunt down and analyze ghosts in this new series in the Rising Stars universe. Lionel’s latest case gives him a unique point of view, but sends his clients screaming. All the while, Lionel draws closer and closer to a force greater than he ever imagined! Great new Rising Stars action is brought to you by Fiona Avery (Amazing Fantasy, Araña) and Staz Johnson (Spider-Man/Doctor Octopus)!
name: Voices of the Dead #2

volume.name: Rising Stars: Voices Of The Dead

description: Lionel Zerb, the Rising Stars "Special" who communes with the dead, has met his match. His minions have been searching for another realm where spirits must go when they finally dissipate from this plane of existence. At long last, one of his minions has found a home where not even the dead dare to enter. Lionel's first encounter with something even MORE frightening than the spirit world begins!

description: With the Red Hood's identity revealed to be Jason Todd, the Robin who died, Batman searches for clues as to how the body of Jason Todd was removed from it's coffin.  As Batman collects evidence, flashbacks piece together the story of Jason Todd.  As Batman looks, the answer becomes more and more apparent, the shocking ending of this issue will change what you thought you knew about the Body that was supposed to be in the coffin!  Don't miss this issue!
name: Show Me Yesterday, For I Can't Find Today  : A Robins Tale

description: Ghost-talker Lionel Zerb struggles with the weight of the psychic world as he tries to determine what the vortex within the House on Stansbury Lane really contains. Why are spirits ripped to shreds when they go near it? Why was his own consciousness nearly stolen? How can one speak to nothing but a void? Lionel takes a chance in this issue and confronts the great nothingness within the house.
name: Psyche

volume.name: Rising Stars: Voices Of The Dead

description: Lionel Zerb struggles with the weight of the psychic world as he tries to determine what the vortex within the House on Stansbury Lane really wants from him or from anyone, dead or alive. When he finally makes contact, Lionel is asked by a dark entity within the vortex to sacrifice the only thing he has ever loved. Will Lionel give up his happiness in exchange for someone else's greater destiny?
name: Deals with Karma

volume.name: Rising Stars: Voices Of The Dead

description: Lionel Zerb wrestles with inner demons as the conclusion to this six-part mini-series whips to a dramatic conclusion. The choice lies between his childhood-love, Lily, and in finding out if there is more to life than he or any other Special can see. Lionel is about to face an eternity in anguish for the answer to the Universe's greatest questions. Is there a God, an afterlife, a rebirth?
name: Echoes

volume.name: Rising Stars: Voices Of The Dead

description: Michael Roswell is a great musician, a virtuoso pianist Isabella Lombard, Diabolik and Eva should take their place to organize a great shot, but obviously neither can substitute for a musician. The King of Terror will have to study a more complex and brilliant than ever.
name: DIETRO IL SIPARIO

description: The King of Terror is not subject to blackmail. Rebel against any coercion, deny any influence, oppose those who try to handle it is to rule his life. But at the same time Diabolik knows that the rules can and sometimes must be broken. As will be forced to do in this strange adventure.
name: DIABOLIK DEVE PAGARE

description: Diabolik scored yet another coup and media unleashed against Ginko, accusing him of incompetence and even cowardly. When the inspector feels it no longer even the support of his superiors, he decided to throw in the towel and retire to private life. How will the King of Terror to surrender his best enemy?
name: LA RESA DI GINKO

description: Hardcase visits J.D. Hunt and scares him into revealing the location of Rex Mundi. When he goes to the secret location, Hardcase learns that it was a set-up because the building explodes. Hardcase then speaks to Tech of the Solution to find out where the Quattro may be. Shadowmage informs him where Death Dance and Meathook are. Hardcase goes to visit them and they attack him, thinking they're in a fight. After Hardcase resolves the confusion, Death Dance and Meathook informs him where they could find Rex. Meanwhile, the new Choice that Hardcase inadvertently 'created' by altering the time stream arrives at Hardcase's office to find him. At the same time, the real Choice arrives from Godwheel to find Hardcase's home in shambles.
name: Mundiquest, Part III of IV: The Set Up

description: Hardcase arrives to the mountain that Death Dance and Meathook directed him to find Rex Mundi. While there, creatures made of the earth rise from the ground and attack Hardcase. They battle for a while and Hardcase contemplates what the Alternate told him before, that he has powers he has no idea about. Suddenly the creatures in contact with him become frozen. Defeating the creatures, Hardcase finds a way into the mountain and then underground, to the lair of Rex Mundi. Meanwhile, the original Choice arrives to find Hardcase. She is surprised to find another woman taking the Choice identity, which makes her angry. She believes that the Choice Corporation cloned her and they both fight.
name: Mundiquest, Part IV of IV: The Threshold

description: Hardcase finally confront Rex Mundi. Rex Mundi captures him and explains to him his origin. Rex Mundi is the world's first true ultra and he created the Alternate out of his own body, making an equal. The Alternate didn't agree with Rex Mundi's agenda of controlling the world and destroying all ultras because they were a risk to his agenda. The Alternate, Regina, opposed Rex Mundi since then. Rex Mundi created NM-E to be his ultra destroyer. While Rex reveals this information, Hardcase realizes that he's much more powerful than he thought. He uses this newfound power to time travel and stop his past self from saving the Squad. When that occurs, the original Choice kills the newest Choice. Hardcase arrives back in Rex Mundi's lair and is disrupted by an attack from the Alternate in NM-E's armor. The battle is waged as they release Hardcase from the lair. Realizing the fight was not his anymore and that he defeated Rex in his own way, Hardcase goes back to his office to find Choice there, ready to start a life together with him.
name: Mundiquest: The Confrontation

  2. "The Man Who Destroyed Krypton!" written by Otto Binder, penciled and inked by Al Plastino.

description: The Villains United want a piece of Gotham, and Black Mask is just the man to deliver it. Batman has his hands full with the criminals of Gotham, but before he can neutralize Deathstroke and company, Red Hood plans to take matters into his own hands!  Batman's paths cross with the Red Hood and before you know it, they will soon be watching the same situation go down, with the same reaction!
name: Franchise, Part 1 of 2: Supply Side Economics  : Bombastic Battle!

description:
Spend some time with the kids of Springfield or maybe just a really strange day in the life of Ralph Wiggum. Or discover what happens when, through a weird twist of fate, Milhouse becomes invisible (at least that's what Bart tells him). And evil super villains best beware (yes, you, Doctor Colossus) when the Simpsons' cat, Snowball II, gains superpowers and becomes the Supercat of Springfield!

  1. The Supercat Of Springfield! (Snowball becomes a super-kitty!)
  2. "The Invisible Nerd!" (Milhouse becomes invisible - or so he thinks)
  3. 24 Hours In The Life Of Ralph Wiggum!

description:
Story 1: Primal Appearance

Kevin Green becomes Prime, saving a falling airplane that he accidentally destroyed. He uses his power to stop the lecherous gym teacher in his school.

Story 2: From On High

Yrial and the Chieftan speak when she notices a vampire killing a priest in the church. Yrial stalks the vampire, who becomes frantic and accidentally impales himself while falling. Yrial returns back to the sky, telling the Chieftan no living soul has seen her.

Story 3: The Last Mission

The Squad stop a group of terrorists that are holding a junior high school hostage.

Story 4: Once Upon A Bedtime...

Mantra tells a bedtime story to Evie, recounting the history between Archimage and Boneyard.

Story 5: Freex

Boom Boy and Anything find Pressure and invite her to come with them.

description: You asked for it! Hot on the tail of Richard K. Morgan's searing comics debut comes the further dark exploits of Natasha Romanova, the original Black Widow. Some say she's a traitor, some say she's a murderer…and what most say about her isn't even printable. But nobody denies that the former Cold War spy is a force to be reckoned with. The last man foolish enough to send killers after her paid the highest price, but his friends on Capitol Hill will ensure that Natasha doesn't get off easy…and not even Col. Nick Fury can protect her this time. Meanwhile, the survivors of Natasha's last tirade start coming back to haunt her…and they're starting to join forces. Also featuring a guest appearance by Daredevil! Richard K. Morgan is the Phillip K. Dick Award-winning sci-fi author of Altered Carbon, Broken Angels, and Market Forces. Returning to BLACK WIDOW is comics legend Bill Sienkiewicz (ELEKTRA: ASSASSIN), joined by Eisner Award-nominated artist Sean Phillips (Sleeper). Read the red-hot sequel to the limited series praised by Entertainment Weekly, Ain't It Cool News, SFX Magazine and more!
name: The Things They Say About Her

volume.name: Black Widow: The Things They Say About Her

volume.name: Black Widow: The Things They Say About Her

name: Help and Those Who Need It

volume.name: Black Widow: The Things They Say About Her

description: Award-winning collaborators Richard K. Morgan, Sean Phillips, and Bill Sienkiewicz rev up the tension when Natasha tracks down a girl held prisoner in a heavily fortified jungle compound. The Black Widow must contend with sadistic foes who perform experiments on helpless children, but can she do it alone, especially when old enemies close in, vowing to get even? Meanwhile, Matt Murdock comes to the aid of a captured Nick Fury, but his actions may do more harm than good! Don't miss the red-hot sequel to the limited series praised by Entertainment Weekly, Ain't It Cool News, SFX Magazine and more!
name: Women and Children First

volume.name: Black Widow: The Things They Say About Her

description: The Black Widow stands alone with all her enemies arrayed before her. Will she be able to save herself, much less the captured Nick Fury, before it’s too late?
name: Do You Feel Better Now?

volume.name: Black Widow: The Things They Say About Her

description: It’s the action-packed endgame in La Havana between the Black Widow and the agents of North! Will Natasha, branded public enemy number one, by the United States government itself, be able to make it out alive and redeem her name? And even if she can find redemption, will she want to?
name: Welcome to the Game

volume.name: Black Widow: The Things They Say About Her

As Constantine tries to figure out what it means, the brutal African war-mage known as Mako hits London - and he's taking no prisoners...

Continue in Justice League of Aliens.

Constantine and his all-too-familiar guide take the back road into Hell as John searches for the kidnapped soul of a loved one. But he finds an especially dangerous opponent from his past who knows him as well as he knows himself.

But sulfurous wastes and succubi still bar their path, and the demon has saved the best lie for last, the one that destroys every last possibility of success.

description:
Bart and Lisa battle it out when the Android's Dungeon sponsors a science contest at Springfield Elementary. It's brain vs. Bart in a tale that leads to the deepest, darkest depths of scientific genius and depravity... kinda! Then, Lisa puts her super sleuthing to the test when she attempts to uncover the mystery behind Homer's missing breakfast. Finally, Bart's pet pachyderm, Stampy, returns!

description:
This "80 Page Giant G-63" reprints some of Lois' strangest adventures to date.

  1. Cover by Curt Swan and Neal Adams.
  2. "Lois Lane's Super-Brain!" Reprinted from Superman's Girl Friend Lois Lane #27 (with 2 new panels) Lois gets super smarts and a cranium to match. What will Superman think?
  3. "The Superwoman of Metropolis!" Reprinted from Superman's Girl Friend Lois Lane #8. Lois gets super-powers for her birthday.
  4. "Lois Lane, Slave Girl!" Reprinted from Superman's Girl Friend Lois Lane #33. Lois ends up in ancient Rome.
  5. "The Widow in Black!" Reprinted from Superman's Girl Friend Lois Lane #32. Lois wants a tougher assignment, so Perry assigns her to find the Playboy Poisoner.
  6. "The Madam Jekyll of Metropolis!" Reprinted from Superman's Girl Friend Lois Lane #36. Red Kryptonite turns Lois into a Jekyll and Hyde.
  7. "Lois Lane, Hag!" Reprinted from Superman's Girl Friend Lois Lane #40. While investigating a youth serum fraud, Lois becomes ... old?
name: The Strange Lives of Lois Lane!

description:
Lola Bunny sets out to beat the pants off the pizza-slinging competition in the Miss Delivery Girl Pageant; Pete Puma slinks into Foghorn Leghorn''s territory; and Sylvester and son learn things the hard way at the local library!

  3. Punishin' Pete Puma (Foghorn Leghorn, Pete Puma, Barnyard Dawg : Pete, now an escapee, wants a free meal - maybe a chicken dinner a la Foghorn?)
